    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="707"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d707">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Japanese Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your excellency’s note of August 24 last on the subject of the treaty
                    annexing Korea to the Empire of Japan, signed on the 22d ultimo.</p>
                <p>While I am constrained by the great importance of the interests of American
                    citizens in Korea to make all necessary reservations as to their rights and
                    privileges, I beg to inform your excellency that the Government of the United
                    States is gratified to note the assurances already given by the Imperial
                    Japanese Government concerning matters relating to foreigners and foreign trade
                    in Korea.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
